>> title: Yogurt-Herb Sauce
>> cuisine: Middle Eastern
>> tags: sauce, gluten-free, soy-free
>> servings: 8
>> yield: 1.5 cups
>> storage_days: 5
>> storage_method: refrigerated
>> reheat: Serve cold.

-- A cooling, tangy sauce for the shawarma bowls. No cooking -- just stir.

In a #bowl{}, stir together @plain greek yogurt{1%cup}, @fresh lemon juice{1%tbsp}, @garlic{1%clove}(grated -- a microplane is ideal here), @fresh dill{2%tbsp}(chopped), @fresh mint{1%tbsp}(chopped), @olive oil{1%tbsp}, and @kosher salt{1/2%tsp}.

Thin with @water{1%tbsp} at a time until it's spoonable but not runny.

Let it rest ~{10%minutes} so the garlic and herbs bloom, then taste and adjust salt and lemon.

-- Used in: chicken shawarma bowls, wraps, as a vegetable dip
